The documentation website under guide/ loads Mermaid (https://mermaid.js.org/,
MIT License) from the jsDelivr CDN at runtime to render diagrams. Mermaid is not
vendored or redistributed in this repository or in the distributed plugin; only
the public docs site references it (pinned to an exact version with a Subresource
Integrity hash).

The documentation website (index.html and guide/) loads GoatCounter's count.js
(https://www.goatcounter.com/, ISC License) for cookieless, privacy-friendly
visitor analytics. Unlike Mermaid, count.js is vendored into this repository at
assets/count.js (its ISC license header retained) and served same-origin from
the docs site — no third-party executable script runs on the pages. It is a docs
site asset only and is not part of the distributed plugin. The analysis reports
load no analytics and remain fully self-contained.
